# 🚀 Protocol: How to Create a GitHub Repository (Interface + Terminal)

This protocol explains how to create and set up a GitHub repository using both the **GitHub interface (web)** and the **terminal (local machine)**.  

---

## ✅ Step 1: Create Repository on GitHub (Interface)

1. Log in to [GitHub](https://github.com/).
2. Click **➕ New Repository**.
3. Enter a **repository name** (e.g., `churning_prediction_modeling`).
4. Add a short description and choose **Public/Private**.
5. ⚠️ Leave **“Initialize with README” unchecked** if you already have local files.
6. Click **Create Repository**.  
   👉 Copy the repo URL (HTTPS):  
https://github.com/<username>/<repo_name>.git

---

## ✅ Step 2: Prepare Local Project (Terminal)

1. Navigate to your base GitHub folder:
```bash
cd ~/Documents/GitHub
Create your project folder with a professional structure:
mkdir -p churning_prediction_modeling/{data/raw,data/processed,notebooks,scripts,results/figures,results/tables,docs}
cd churning_prediction_modeling
Create initial files:
touch README.md requirements.txt .gitignore
📂 Recommended Folder Layout
churning_prediction_modeling/
│── data/
│   ├── raw/          # Original datasets (read-only)
│   └── processed/    # Cleaned/feature-engineered data
│
│── notebooks/        # Jupyter notebooks (exploration & modeling)
│
│── scripts/          # Python scripts / helper functions
│
│── results/
│   ├── figures/      # Plots, charts, dashboards
│   └── tables/       # Summaries, output tables
│
│── docs/             # Extra documentation, references
│── README.md         # Project overview
│── requirements.txt  # Python dependencies
│── .gitignore        # Files/folders to ignore in Git

## ✅ Step 3: Initialise Git and Link Remote
Initialise Git:
git init
Link GitHub remote:
git remote add origin https://github.com/<username>/<repo_name>.git
Verify:
git remote -v

## ✅ Step 4: First Commit & Push
Stage all files:
git add .
Commit:
git commit -m "Initial commit with project structure"
Rename branch & push:
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

## 🔄 Ongoing Workflow
Stage changes:
git add .
Commit changes:
git commit -m "Your message"
Push to GitHub:
git push
